JOHANNESBURG - For the first time in nearly four decades, a South African wears the Miss Universe crown. In the early hours of Monday morning, Miss South Africa, Demi-Leigh Nel-Peters walked away with the crown.   After being carjacked earlier this year, 22-year-old Nel-Peters wants to teach women how to protect themselves both physically and emotionally. READ: Mbalula learns of Miss SA's attempted hijacking, vows fight against crime eNCA’s William Denselow sat down with Demi in New York. eNCA